 "components": {
  "task_instruction": "You are a precise text classifier. Read the input text and assign it to exactly one of the categories defined below.",
  "label::automatic_top_up": "Questions or issues about setting up, editing, or troubleshooting recurring or scheduled automatic top-ups (where funds are added to the account automatically on a schedule or triggered by conditions like low balance) belong here. If the concern is about a top-up happening automatically instead of being a one-time, user-initiated action, assign this category; otherwise, use 'topping_up_by_card' for manual or one-off card top-ups.",
  "label::balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer": "",
  "label::beneficiary_not_allowed": "",
  "label::cancel_transfer": "",
  "label::card_payment_fee_charged": "",
  "label::card_payment_not_recognised": "",
  "label::declined_cash_withdrawal": "",
  "label::exchange_rate": "",
  "label::exchange_via_app": "",
  "label::failed_transfer": "",
  "label::get_disposable_virtual_card": "",
  "label::get_physical_card": "",
  "label::passcode_forgotten": "",
  "label::pending_top_up": "",
  "label::pending_transfer": "",
  "label::receiving_money": "",
  "label::reverted_card_payment?": "",
  "label::top_up_by_cash_or_cheque": "",
  "label::top_up_reverted": "",
  "label::topping_up_by_card": "Questions or issues about adding money to an account using a card (including credit, debit, or prepaid cards), whether by the account holder or by someone else (e.g., a friend), belong here. If the input asks about any specific top-up method using a card, or how someone else can add funds to the account, assign this category. Do not use for top-ups set to happen automatically or on a schedule; those go to 'automatic_top_up'.",
  "label::transfer_fee_charged": "",
  "label::transfer_into_account": "",
  "label::transfer_timing": "",
  "label::verify_my_identity": "",
  "label::verify_source_of_funds": "",
  "boundary_rules": "If the input concerns the PIN (e.g., where to find it or access it) for a card, assign 'get_physical_card'; if it concerns forgetting or resetting a code (including passcode), assign 'passcode_forgotten'.\n\nIf the issue is a transfer that fails because the beneficiary (recipient) is not permitted or allowed (e.g., recipient is blocked, restricted, or not supported), assign 'beneficiary_not_allowed'; if it is a transfer that fails for any other reason (e.g., technical or unspecified error), assign 'failed_transfer'.\n\nIf the input describes a transfer that is still pending, delayed, or not yet completed, assign 'pending_transfer'; if it asks about general processing times or transfer duration but does not mention a specific pending transfer, assign 'transfer_timing'."
